OL,6,FMr Kalia says his health and
OL,7,Frelationships with his family have
OL,8,Fsuffered as a result of his wrongful
OL,9,Fconviction.
OL,11,FHe says his daughters have also
OL,12,Fstruggled with the long-term impact of
OL,13,Fhis wrongful conviction.
OL,15,F"I feel empathy for my children
OL,16,Fbecause they've had to go through a
OL,17,Flot. They're going through counselling
OL,18,Findividually at the moment. It's
OL,19,Ftrauma that hasn't ended yet...
OL,20,FThere's still no closure," Parmod
OL,21,Ftells us.
